               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors (often only the second component); incipit of Texts I and II; title of Text I-2; incipit of the sections of the daily readings (homilies, absolution prayers, miracles and ʾarke); selected words or parts of words in ʾarke; words “sälam” and “sǝbḥat” in Text II; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
A few groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I; a few groups of lines of the incipit of Texts I-2 to I-8.&#xD;
The first and the last letters or every second letter are rubricated in the nomina sacra on fols. 29vb, 50rb, 61ra, 69rab, 83rb.</rubric>
